saw.lzw-binary.name: saw.lzw-binary

encode.description:
Encodes the string as an LZW compressed binary stream...except
because we can't really use binary in javascript we are using the unicode
character specified by the decimal code output by the algorithm in each place

return.description: result a hash table with ascii letters as keys

getDic.description: Returns a pre-popuated dictionary to begin encoding

return.description: num the length of the string in bytes

strSize.description: Utitilty method that returns the size of a unicode string in bytes

params.description: An Event Facade object with      the following attribute specific properties added:	<dl>		<dt>prevVal</dt>		<dd>The value of the attribute, prior to it being set</dd>		<dt>newVal</dt>		<dd>The value the attribute is to be set to</dd>		<dt>attrName</dt>		<dd>The name of the attribute being set</dd>		<dt>subAttrName</dt>		<dd>If setting a property within the attribute's value,           the name of the sub-attribute property being set</dd>	</dl>

timeChange.name: timeChange
timeChange.description: Fires when the value for the configuration attribute 'time' is changed. You can listen for the event using the on method if you wish to be notified before the attribute's value has changed, or using the after method if you wish to be notified after the attribute's value has changed.

_syncTime.description:
This method syncs the value of time object,
including building the strings for 12hr and 24hr
also fires a 'timechange' event
